Kazzinc is a Kazakhstani mining company founded in 1997, when a majority stake was privatised to Swiss commodity trader Glencore.[1] It has 6 mines and several smelters, and produces zinc, lead and copper, and also has interests in gold and silver mining.[1] Kazzinc sponsors Kazzinc-Torpedo, a Kazakhstani ice hockey team. 
